  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing Border Security in Burkina Faso</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">With the overall objective of strengthening security, stability and social cohesion along the most sensitive borders and of mitigating increasing violence through trust building activities between authorities and populations at Burkina Faso&#x2019;s borders East and Southern borders, this project will enhance the Border Police&#x2019;s operational and technical capacities and improve the engagement of cross-border communities to secure its borders against terrorists. IOM will work in close cooperation and coordination with the Government of Burkina Faso, both at the central and the local level as well as with key international actors in the target country such as the Directorate of the Border Police, the Ministry of Security, INTERPOL, and other agencies of the United Nations system. Coordination mechanisms will be set up with all stakeholders engaged in relevant on-going projects to ensure that synergies are maximised.</narrative>
  </description>
